@page "/"

<PageTitle>HR Job Portal - Home</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-4">
    <div class="jumbotron">
        <h1 class="display-4">Welcome to HR Job Portal</h1>
        <p class="lead">Your one-stop platform for job seekers and employers</p>
        <hr class="my-4">
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-5">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h2>About This Project</h2>
            <p>
                HR Job Portal is a comprehensive web application designed to streamline the job application process. 
                Built with ASP.NET Core and Blazor, this platform offers a seamless experience for both job seekers and employers.
            </p>
            
            <h3 class="mt-4">Key Features</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>User Authentication</strong> - Secure login and registration system</li>
                <li><strong>Profile Management</strong> - Create and update your professional profile</li>
                <li><strong>Education History</strong> - Track your academic achievements</li>
                <li><strong>Resume Upload</strong> - Store and manage your resume documents</li>
                <li><strong>Job Listings</strong> - Browse through available job opportunities</li>
                <li><strong>Application Tracking</strong> - Monitor the status of your job applications</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3 class="mt-4">Technology Stack</h3>
            <p>
                This application is built using:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>ASP.NET Core 8.0</li>
                <li>Blazor Server for interactive UI</li>
                <li>Entity Framework Core for data access</li>
                <li>SQL Server for database storage</li>
                <li>Bootstrap for responsive design</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3 class="mt-4">Getting Started</h3>
            <p>
                To get started with HR Job Portal:
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>Create an account or log in if you already have one</li>
                <li>Complete your profile with personal and educational information</li>
                <li>Upload your resume</li>
                <li>Browse available jobs and apply to positions that match your skills</li>
                <li>Track your applications through the My Applications page</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
